n of land and culture contributed to the sustainability of hawaiian agriculture and society before european contact and working to make fertilizer applications more efficient and less environmentally damaging especially in rapidly growing economies he is a fellow of the national academy of sciences and the american academy of arts and sciences and was awarded the 2010 japan prize he is director of the emmett interdisciplinary program in environment and resources and co director of the first nations futures institute stanford departments biological sciences publications cover agriculture in brazil impacts costs and opportunities for a sustainable future luiz martinelli rosamond l naylor peter vitousek paulo moutinho current opinion in environmental sustainability vol 2 2010 html+ cover nutrient imbalances in agricultural development peter vitousek rosamond l naylor et al science vol 324 2009 html+ cover business strategies for conservation on private lands koa forestry as a case study josh goldstein james b friday pamela matson rosamond l naylor peter vitousek proceedings for the national academy of sciences vol 103 26 2006 html+ events & presentations historical traces of land use change in hawaii february 3 2005 fsi stanford forum peter vitousek research programs & projects globalization trade and the environment the case of brazil fsi stanford fse project integrated studies of sustainability land water systems of the yaqui basin fsi stanford fse project completed search fse search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages recent commentary new fse publication examines the impacts costs and opportunities for sustainable agriculture in brazil december 2 2010 fsi stanford fse news balancing act in global fertilizer use science report june 29 2009 fsi stanford fse news cesp senior fellows receive funding from the presidential fund to support the launch of the new program on food security and the environment febru